How do u cope with judgement can’t believe how people treat u even family members I’ve gone from hard working family man to a total dependant disabled half of a man. My wife has been amazing virtually does everything for me but my parents and friends have changed they seem embarrassed to be seen with me and moan when I say I can’t do things. I can hardly walk because of pain in my feet. Plus my hands shot to so can only use crutches short distances like 10 metres max. But my parents are expecting me to walk across beaches or climb loads of steps and say I’m dramatising things when I say I can’t. Getting fed up of it to be honest.

This picture of me when I was just starting the sober thing. Full year sober now. This guy is my whole entire world. Been with me since 2015. Seen me fall and get back up. Somedays I would rather be alone and just spend my entire day with him. Pure bliss.

This is my first post so thanks for back for me as I’m desperate for information and relief from this horrible thing called Neuropathy!  My journey started two years ago when I was put in the hospital for having a stomach infection… They immediately gave me IV Levaquin and as soon as it hit my system I knew something was wrong because my whole body went numb and got a horrible taste in my mouth. I asked them to discontinue the medication as it was making me sick but they would not and said I needed it for my stomach infection and the numbness feeling was just because I was dehydrated… A week after being in the hospital being given Levaquin daily I was released and had horrible numbness in my hands and feet… This never went away and has gotten worse in my feet and lower legs. I did start feeling my hands again about a year ago but my feet are constantly burning, pins and needles, feels like I’m walking on blocks and swell so bad, I can hardly walk. I have a job that requires me to travel 75% of the time all over the world so I am really close to not being able to do this.  I just keep smiling and walk slow even though I’m dying on the inside.  I’ve had all tests known - MRI, electric nerve tests, even a spinal tap and no one can help me.  I’m only 42 and should not have lost if quality life like this.  😞 if anyone could share anything that really helped them, I’d love to try it. I know Levaquin caused this but I don’t know how to reverse it…￼

I have just been diagnosed with polyneuropathy after having a nerve conduction test. I now have an appointment with a Neurologist. Can you tell me what happens now? How do they find out what caused it? This sounds like a very scarey disease that there is no relief from so I am trying to learn all I can.

Side note: neuropathy throughout my body, worse on left side. Surgery was on left outer ankle of left foot. Only the left nerve was cut; but my whole foot is now 10x worse then before😭

A drunk is sitting in a bar and asks the bartender, "Where's the bathroom at?" The bartender says, "Go down the hall and make a right." Well, all of a sudden, everybody at the bar hears this loud scream coming from the bathroom, and they wonder about what's going on in there. A few minutes go by, and again, everybody at the bar hears another loud scream that came out of the bathroom. This time, the bartender decides to investigate, and he goes into the bathroom to see what the drunk is screaming about. He opens the door and asks the drunk, "What's all the screaming about in here? You are scaring all my customers away." The drunk whines, "I'm sitting on the toilet and every time I go to flush it, something comes up and squeezes the heck out of my gonads!" With that, the bartender looks in and says, "No wonder! You're sitting on a mop bucket, you idiot!!"
